wdi-ER.H2O.INTR.PC.def: Renewable internal freshwater resources flows refer to internal renewable resources (internal river flows and groundwater from rainfall) in the country. Renewable internal freshwater resources per capita are calculated using the World Bank's population estimates.
wdi-ER.H2O.INTR.PC.name: Renewable internal freshwater resources per capita
wdi-ER.H2O.INTR.PC.source: Food and Agriculture Organization, AQUASTAT data.
